cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.OH, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the performance analysis of a dual-hop relay transmission system, which involves the study of information transmission and coding. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the impact of pointing errors on the performance of mixed RF/FSO dual hop transmission systems, which is relevant to the design and optimization of wireless networks. 
3. cs.OH (Optimization and Control): The paper presents closed-form expressions for various performance metrics, which involves optimization and control of the system parameters. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the performance analysis of a system composed of asymmetric RF/FSO links, which involves the study of systems and control. 
5. cs.PF (Performance): The paper focuses on the performance analysis of a dual-hop relay transmission system, which is relevant to the evaluation and optimization of system performance.
